Select a Dataset

To get great results with your models and predictions, start by preparing the data you want to analyze in your dataset. 
Your dataset must contain a minimum number of rows for Einstein to analyze.
For model creation, you can use a dataset with a predicate (row-level security).
A model is based on a snapshot of the data in the CRM Analytics dataset.

Consider selecting datasets that are more static than dynamic.
To select a dataset:

Find the dataset you want to use to create the model.
Open the dropdown on the CRM Analytics dataset.
Click Create Model.

Configure Model

Selecting a Dataset for Model Creation
To create a model, your dataset must contain a minimum number of rows for Einstein to analyze, as described in Einstein Discovery Capacities and Requirements.
For model creation, you can use a dataset with a predicate (row-level security). Your access must be at least 400 rows of data.
